Interface DiscoveryClassifier

  • All Superinterfaces:
    PluginComponent, PropertyConfigurable

    public interface DiscoveryClassifier
extends PluginComponent, PropertyConfigurable
    This is the primary interface implemented by all automated sensitive data discovery classifiers.

    • Method Detail

      • getClassificationTarget

        DiscoveryClassifier.Target getClassificationTarget()
        This method determines the type of classifier the class implements.
        Returns:
        The type of input this classifier expects, refer to classify(List) below.

      • multiConfigSupport

        default boolean multiConfigSupport()
        Returning a true from this method indicates that this classifier's configure method may be called multiple times, and the classifier will store and apply all configurations. This allows a single classifier to check multiple regular expression patterns, processing a non-match only for inputs where none of the patterns match.
        Returns:
        Whether the classifier supports multiple configurations

      • classify

        DiscoveryClassifier.ClassificationResult classify(java.util.List<java.lang.String> values)
        The contents of the values list depends on the Target of the classifier: PATH - Some number of path names describing the location of the data in the schema or data format. For databases, this will be schema_name, table_name, column_name. For delimited files, it will be a single value containing the field name. DATA - This will a list of actual data values. DATA_DATES - This will a list of LocalDateTime objects constructed from the dates in the data columns. GENERIC_TYPE - This will be a list of two value: type and a numeric length of the column or field. SQL_TYPE - Just an idea for now - a classifier that sees the raw SQL type, would be DB specific.
        Parameters:
        values - The values to classify.
        Returns:
        The classification results
